-- Taiwan Stocks: Chimei Innolux, Chroma ATE, Epistar, Everlight
-- B y   W e i y i   L i m
-- 2012-02-22T06:23:22Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-02-22/taiwan-equity-movers-chimei-innolux-chroma-ate-tpk-holding.html
Shares of the following companies
had  unusual  moves in  Taiwan trading . Stock symbols are in
parentheses and prices are as of the close in Taipei.  The benchmark Taiex Index rose 1 percent to 8,001.68.  Light-emitting diode makers:  Epistar Corp. (2448)  (2448 TT) jumped
7 percent to NT$80, the highest close since July 8.  Everlight
Electronics Co. (2393)  (2393 TT) increased 4.1 percent to NT$68.50.
Research firm LEDinside said in a report dated yesterday it’s a
“matter of time” before LED lights become more affordable for
consumers.  Chimei Innolux Corp. (3481)  (3481 TT),  Taiwan ’s largest flat-panel
maker, retreated 2 percent to NT$14.90, the lowest close since
Feb. 2. The company’s foreign debt totaled NT$50 billion ($1.7
billion) to NT$60 billion, most of which is loans owed to
 China ’s state banks, Commercial Times reported, without saying
where it got the information. Eddie Chen, spokesman for the
company, declined to comment on the report.  Chroma ATE Inc. (2360)  (2360 TT) dropped 2.5 percent to NT$67.80,
the lowest close since Feb. 7. The electronics maker was cut to
“neutral” from “overweight” at HSBC Holdings Plc.  Foxconn Technology Co. (2354)  (2354 TT) surged 6.7 percent to
NT$136, the biggest advance since Feb. 8. The casing maker was
rated “outperform” in new coverage at Credit Suisse Group AG.  To contact the reporter on this story:
